---
target: build/builder
version: 1
validations:
  - name: builder-module-exists
    type: folder_check
    path: src/builder

  - name: builder-structure-defined
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the builder module defines:
      1. A Builder type with dependencies: projectRoot, agent, stateManager, parser, gitManager, config
      2. A BuildOptions type with: Target, Force, DryRun, OutputDir, ProfileName
      3. Methods: Build, Clean, Validate
      4. A constructor that accepts all dependencies via injection
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/**"]

  - name: builder-uses-dag
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that the builder:
      1. Uses the graph module to build a DAG from targets
      2. Uses topological sort to determine build order
      3. Respects dependencies (builds dependencies before dependents)
      4. Stops building on first failure
      5. Supports dry run mode (prints plan without executing)
      6. Uses the agent interface (not a concrete agent) for building
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/**"]

  - name: builder-runs-schema-validation
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that the builder runs schema validation as Step 0 of every build and validate operation:
      1. Build calls ValidateAllSpecs before loading targets
      2. Build calls ValidateConfig before proceeding
      3. If any error-severity violations are found, build aborts with clear error listing all violations
      4. Validate also runs schema validation before running validations
      5. Schema validation errors include file paths and field names
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/**"]

  - name: builder-profile-resolution
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify per-target agent profile resolution:
      1. CLI --profile flag (opts.ProfileName) takes highest priority
      2. Per-target profile field in .ic frontmatter is second priority
      3. "default" profile is the final fallback
      4. Different targets in the same build can use different agents/models
      5. Profile is resolved via config.GetProfile and agent created via CreateFromProfile
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/**"]

  - name: builder-tests-use-mock-agent
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify builder tests:
      1. Use a mock agent (not a real CLI agent)
      2. Test the full build pipeline with mock responses
      3. Test dry run mode
      4. Test force rebuild
      5. Test dependency ordering
      6. Test failure handling (agent returns error -> build stops)
      7. Test schema validation abort (malformed spec -> build doesn't start)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/builder/**"]

  - name: builder-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: cd src && uv run pytest builder/ -v
    exit_code: 0
---

# Builder Validations

The builder is the most complex module, integrating all others. Tests must use mocks for the agent and state manager to be fast and deterministic. The key invariants: schema validation runs first, dependency order is respected, failures halt the build, and dry run never invokes the agent.
